\date{2024-03-07}
\title{subsheaf of units}
\taxon{definition}
\author{trebor}
\import{common}

\p{
  Given a sheaf #{\sheaf{O}} of rings, we can define a subsheaf #{\sheaf{O}^\times} consisting of the invertible elements, i.e. #{\section(U, \sheaf{O}^\times) = \section(U, \sheaf{O})^\times}. This is the \strong{subsheaf of units}.
}

\p{
  This can be equivalently expressed as a pullback of #{\sheaf{O} \times \sheaf{O} \xto{(f,g) \mapsto f g} \sheaf{O}} and #{1 \xto{1} \sheaf{O}}.
}
